Apart from these, some unique asymmetric silica-based nanoparticles can be fabricated by surface-controlled nucleation and growth. Generally, the nucleation and growth method are determined by the overall Gibbs free energy, which can be represented as Δσ=σ2-s-σ1-s+σ1-2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
